# Introduction to Ruby and Ruby-On-Rails

Here's a collection of resources that I found useful for anyone wanting to learn Ruby / Ruby-On-Rails.
It aims to be a relatively quick way of getting into it, but free and to be consumed at your own pace.

1. http://jasonkim.ca/projects/just_enough_ruby_to_get_by/
2. https://www.railstutorial.org/book
3. https://guides.rubyonrails.org/getting_started.html
4. https://www.pluralsight.com/courses/code-school-rails-for-zombies

Weekly newsletter:
https://rubyweekly.com

Slack for chatting + wiki pages
https://www.rubyonrails.link/
https://github.com/railslink/resources/wiki

